OL,3,CChancellor Reeves warned of 'tough'
OL,4,Ctrade-offs ahead of spending review
OL,6,FIt added: "The Government should
OL,7,Fprioritise investment based on areas
OL,8,Fof particularly acute historical under-
OL,9,Finvestment, and the future impacts on
OL,10,Fliving standards and economic growth.
OL,12,F"Investment that is likely to be well
OL,13,Ftargeted across both of these criteria
OL,14,Fincludes social investment in housing
OL,15,Fand health, with investment in the
OL,16,Fprison system and well-targeted
OL,17,Ftransport infrastructure projects in
OL,18,Fthe UK's second cities being secondary
OL,19,Fpriorities."
