OL,3,CChancellor Reeves warned of 'tough'
OL,4,Ctrade-offs ahead of spending review
OL,6,FRachel Reeves told the BBC in March
OL,7,Fthat "we can't just carry on like we
OL,8,Fhave been, spending on the same things
OL,9,Fthat the previous government spent on".
OL,11,FJames Smith, research director at the
OL,12,FResolution Foundation said that the
OL,13,Fupcoming review "offers a unique
OL,14,Fopportunity to reverse Britain's
OL,15,Fterrible record on public investment"
OL,16,Fbut warned that "tough trade offs lie
OL,17,Fahead" for the Chancellor.
